    "body": "### Problem\n\nI tried creating a decoration provider which sets ephermar inline extmarks. This didn't work though. It just displayed nothing.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean repro.lua\r\n2. `:so`\r\n```lua\r\n-- repro.lua\r\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"test\")\r\nlocal i = 0\r\nlocal cursor\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_decoration_provider(ns, {\r\n    on_win = function(_, win)\r\n        if win ~= vim.api.nvim_get_current_win() then\r\n            return false\r\n        end\r\n\treturn true\r\n    end,\r\n    on_line = function(_, _, bufnr, line)\r\n        local cursor = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)\r\n        if line == cursor[1] - 1 then\r\n            i = i + 1\r\n            vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, line, cursor[2], {\r\n                virt_text = { { i .. \"x\", \"IncSearch\" } },\r\n                virt_text_pos = \"inline\",\r\n                ephemeral = true,\r\n            })\r\n        end\r\n    end,\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect virtual text to show next to the cursor when the screen is being redrawn as it is the case with this\r\n```lua\r\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"test\")\r\nlocal i = 0\r\nlocal cursor\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_decoration_provider(ns, {\r\n    on_win = function(_, win)\r\n        if win ~= vim.api.nvim_get_current_win() then\r\n            return false\r\n        end\r\n\treturn true\r\n    end,\r\n    on_line = function(_, _, bufnr, line)\r\n        local cursor = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)\r\n        if line == cursor[1] - 1 then\r\n            i = i + 1\r\n            vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, line, cursor[2], {\r\n                virt_text = { { i .. \"x\", \"IncSearch\" } },\r\n                virt_text_pos = \"eol\",\r\n                ephemeral = true,\r\n            })\r\n        end\r\n    end,\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0, Build type: Release\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot relevant\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbob",
